com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class StringToMessageTransformer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.StringToMessageTransformer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IToMessageTransformer

    public class StringToMessageTransformer
extends Object
implements IToMessageTransformer
    Transforms a standard FIX formatted String into an IFIXMessage.

    The string format should be the usual tag=value<delimiter> where delimiter defaults to <soh>, but can be set to something different using setDelimiter(char).

    Author:
    John Cameron

        public IFIXMessage toMessage(Object source,
                             IFIXMessage target,
                             boolean dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData)
                      throws IllegalArgumentException,
                             UnsupportedOperationException,
                             NullPointerException
        Clears out message data and replaces the contents with tag and values extracted from the given string.

        The string format should be the usual tag=value<delimiter>

        Specified by:
        toMessage in interface IToMessageTransformer
        Parameters:
        source - String containing tag values
        target - message to be populated
        dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData - True to indicate that no special treatment is to be given to raw data and their associated length fields (that is, they are expected to conform to regular FIX field content and in particular the data field should not contain FIX SOH), false to treat the data field as opaque and use its preceding length field to determine its length. Should be always false for this transformer.
        Returns:
        target, after population
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if source is not a String, or the String is not well formatted
        UnsupportedOperationException - If this form of transformation is not supported by this transformer.
        NullPointerException - if target was null and is needed by a particular implementation of this interface method
